      <h2>What is a 401k?</h2>
      <p>
        A 401(k) is a retirement savings plan sponsored by an employer. It lets workers save and invest a piece of their paycheck before taxes are taken out. Taxes aren’t paid until the money is withdrawn from the account. Since most employers offer 401k matching, they are contributing towards your retirement funds as well. Make sure to take advantage of this. It's like free money!!
      </p>
      <img src="http://www.interest.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/1/2014/04/401k-egg-grass-300x168.jpg">
      <ul>
        <h5> 401(k) Quick Tips </h5>
        <li>At the very least, contribute enough to your 401(k) to get the company match.</li>
        <li>Target-date funds are a popular way to save for retirement.</li>
        <li>If your company goes under, your 401(k) is safe.</li>
      </ul>
